=== SDK Example 12: QuickStart Demo (C#) ===

The Accumulate facade provides the simplest interface to Accumulate.

Connecting to Kermit testnet...

--- Step 1: Create a Wallet ---

[SignatureKeyPair] Imported Ed25519 seed (32 bytes).
[SignatureKeyPair] Derived pubkey (hex): ac2bd34e828a27e96ef8ff65ff0f5a01a55c5b8b9aabac877a8fcaa4a27fd3fc
Created wallet:
  Lite Identity: acc://f7b21b28f591b108134e3661ff6883af3fc4f00b21794962
  Lite Token Account: acc://f7b21b28f591b108134e3661ff6883af3fc4f00b21794962/acme
  Public Key Hash: ac2bd34e828a27e96ef8ff65ff0f5a01...

--- Step 2: Fund the Wallet ---

Requesting funds from faucet (5 times)...
  Faucet 1/5: submitted
  Faucet 2/5: submitted
  Faucet 3/5: submitted
  Faucet 4/5: submitted
  Faucet 5/5: submitted

Waiting 15 seconds for funding...
Balance: 5000000000 units (50.00 ACME)

--- Step 3: Derive ADI URL ---

ADI URL: acc://quickstart-demo-1770949197412.acme
Key Book: acc://quickstart-demo-1770949197412.acme/book
Key Page: acc://quickstart-demo-1770949197412.acme/book/1

--- Step 4: Canonical JSON ---

Input: { z=3, a=1, m=2, nested={ b="hello", a="world" } }
Canonical: {"a":1,"m":2,"nested":{"a":"world","b":"hello"},"z":3}

--- Step 5: Network Endpoints ---

Mainnet V2: https://mainnet.accumulatenetwork.io/v2
Mainnet V3: https://mainnet.accumulatenetwork.io/v3
Testnet V2: https://testnet.accumulatenetwork.io/v2
Testnet V3: https://testnet.accumulatenetwork.io/v3
Devnet V2:  http://localhost:26660/v2
Devnet V3:  http://localhost:26660/v3

--- Step 6: Transaction Type Codes ---

  Code  1: createIdentity
  Code  2: createTokenAccount
  Code  3: sendTokens
  Code  4: createDataAccount
  Code  5: writeData
  Code  8: createToken
  Code  9: issueTokens
  Code 14: addCredits
  Code 15: updateKeyPage
  Code 16: updateAccountAuth
  Code 17: updateKey
  Code 48: remote
  Code 51: syntheticDepositTokens

=== Summary ===

QuickStart Demo achievements:
  1. Created wallet with lite accounts
  2. Funded wallet via faucet
  3. Deri
